ting this form of substance dependence. [Data: Entities (810, 812), Relationships (971)]", "# Cannabis and Its Derivatives Community\n\nThe community centers around cannabis and its derivatives, including marijuana, hashish, and hash oil. These entities are interconnected through their derivation from the cannabis plant and their psychoactive effects. The community also includes the physiological systems affected by marijuana use, such as the cardiovascular and respiratory systems, as well as the potential health risks associated with long-term use.\n\n## Marijuana as the central entity\n\nMarijuana is the most prominent entity in this community, with a high degree of connections to other entities. It is derived from the cannabis plant and is closely related to other cannabis derivatives like hashish and hash oil. Marijuana's widespread use and its effects on various physiological systems make it a key focus of this community. [Data: Entities (902), Relationships (1078, 1081, 1087, 1088, 1089, +more)]\n\n## Hashish and its relationship to marijuana\n\nHashish is a concentrated resin form of cannabis, similar to marijuana, and is derived from the cannabis plant. It contains Δ-9-THC, which is responsible for its psychoactive effects. The relationship between hashish and marijuana highlights the interconnected nature of cannabis derivatives. [Data: Entities (903), Relationships (1078, 1082, 1084)]\n\n## Cannabis plant as the source of derivatives\n\nThe cannabis plant is the source of marijuana, hashish, and hash oil, making it a foundational entity in this community. Its widespread cultivation and the variety of products derived from it underscore its importance. [Data: Entities (906), Relationships (1081, 1082, 1083)]\n\n## Health effects of marijuana use\n\nMarijuana use affects multiple physiological systems, including the cardiovascular and respiratory systems, and increases the risk of cancer. Long-term use also suppresses testosterone secretion, particularly in 